  "body": "We at Polygon have tried creating a **TurboBor** client similar to Erigon by implementing Bor consensus in the Erigon fork - https://github.com/maticnetwork/turbo-bor\r\nAs of now it only supports Syncing and RPC Calls, Mining is not supported yet and it is only available on Testnet (Mumbai) right now (Mainnet testing is in the process).\r\n\r\nNow we are proposing to **Add Bor Consensus Engine to the official Erigon codebase which can support the Polygon chain.** \r\n\r\n**We would appreciate if developers from Erigon, Polygon, or any other community would take a look at what we've done so far and would help us to implement Bor Consensus Engine to Erigonâ€™s official codebase and create a PR for the same.**\r\n\r\nWe believe that together with community collaboration we can achieve our goal quickly and constructively.\r\n\r\n**References:**\r\nTurboBor - [https://github.com/maticnetwork/turbo-bor](https://github.com/maticnetwork/turbo-bor)\r\nPR which implements Bor Consensus to Erigon Folk - [https://github.com/maticnetwork/turbo-bor/pull/1](https://github.com/maticnetwork/turbo-bor/pull/1)\r\nAbout TurboBor - [https://github.com/maticnetwork/turbo-bor/blob/master/README.md](https://github.com/maticnetwork/turbo-bor/blob/master/README.md)",
